<div id="targetspotting">
  <ol>
  <li>Every year road transport consumed the greatest (&#x2026;) of petroleum.
  <list class="set3task1">
  <li><a id="t21">quantity</a></li>
  <li><a id="t22">amount</a></li>
  <li><a id="t23">proportion</a></li>
  <li><a id="t24">number</a></li>
  </list></li>
  
 <li>Petroleum consumption for railways was (&#x2026;) less than for other means of transport.
   <list class="set3task1">
  <li><a id="t25">a lot</a> </li>
   <li><a id="t26">far</a></li>
   <li><a id="t27">many</a></li>
   <li><a id="t28">much</a></li>
   </list></li>
   
   <li>In 1999 road transport consumed (&#x2026;) petroleum than the previous year.
   <list class="set3task1">
  <li><a id="t29">less</a></li>
  <li><a id="t30">fewer</a></li>
  <li><a id="t31">fewer tonnes of</a></li>
  <li><a id="t32">a smaller quantity of</a></li>
  </list></li>
  
  <li>Petroleum consumption by air transport was (&#x2026;) in 1999 than ten years earlier.
     <list class="set3task1">
  <li><a id="t33">many more</a></li>
  <li><a id="t34">much higher</a></li>
  <li><a id="t35">a lot higher</a></li>
  <li><a id="t36">far higher</a></li>
  </list></li>
  
	<li>Over the years railway and water transport consumed (&#x2026;) petroleum.
	<list class="set3task1">
  <li><a id="t37">less and less</a></li>
  <li><a id="t38">smaller and smaller amounts of</a></li>
  <li><a id="t39">fewer and fewer</a></li>
  <li><a id="t40">fewer and fewer tonnes of</a></li>
  </list></li>
  <p class="linespace"></p>
  </ol>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="fb24">
  <p class="feedbacktext">1D. Petroleum is uncountable.</p>
</section>

<section id="fb27">
  <p class="feedbacktext">2C. 'Many' is used for countable nouns, while 'less' is used for uncountable nouns. You cannot use the two together.</p>
</section>

<section id="fb30">
  <p class="feedbacktext">3B. 'Few' and 'fewer' cannot be used with uncountable nouns such as 'petroleum'.</p>
</section>

<section id="fb33">
  <p class="feedbacktext">4A. The missing word refers to the noun 'consumption', which is uncountable.</p>
</section>

<section id="fb39">
  <p class="feedbacktext">5C. Petroleum is uncountable. 'Fewer' can be used only with countable nouns.</p>
</section>

